The paper discusses Deep Gaussian Processes (DGPs), which are a type of machine learning model commonly used in the fields of machine learning, artificial intelligence, computer vision, and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
